collection.name: Black Dragon, AdultCommon
collection.entry: Matte black six-inch scales; Deep-socketed eyes; Broad nasal openings, making its face look like a skull. Segmented horns the curve forward and down, somewhat like a ram's horns, but not as curly. These horns are bone-colored near their bases, but darken to dead black at the tips. Six inches of deteriorated flesh around the horns and cheekbones, as though eaten by acid, leaving only thin layers of hide covering the skull. Most teeth protrude when the mouth is closed. Big spikes stud the lower jaw. Small horns jut from the chin, and a row of hornlets crown the head.
